result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffrey G Colpitts was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Intimidate Witness, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.42.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jeffrey G Colpitts in court with attorney Brett Tyler Kaehne.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Minute sheet. State amends Ct. 1 to Misdemeanor Bail Jumping, amends Ct. 2 to Misdemeanor Intimidation of a Witness. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to amended Counts 1 & 2. Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of amended Counts 1 & 2. Court dismisses Count 3 but reads in for sentencing. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.
Pre-trial conference on July 11, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
Jury trial on July 27, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Brett Tyler Kaehne appeared by phone. Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court questions status of this case. Defense requests that it be set for trial. Set for trial and pre-trial.
State Exh. #1 - certified copy of bond. Offered and received.

Defense waives reading of Information and enters not guilty plea. Atty Kaehne would like this file to track 13-CF-121, would like to see what happens in that case before proceeding on this case. State has no objection. Bond remains as is. Status conference scheduled for January 25, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
